## Per-File Analysis (Architecturally Significant Files)

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/main.py**
**Purpose**: FastAPI application factory and route registration entry point  
**Exports**: FastAPI app instance with CORS middleware and mounted routers  
**Imports**: FastAPI, CORSMiddleware, APIRouter, route modules (characters, stories, memories, family, prompts)  
**Patterns**: Standard FastAPI app factory; CORS middleware for frontend/mobile access; modular route registration via APIRouter; health check endpoint  
**Surprises**: No middleware for request logging, error handling, or request/response transformation visible; route modules imported but registration pattern not shown in signature

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/graphs/story_generator.py**
**Purpose**: LangGraph state machine orchestrating multi-step story generation workflow using LLMs, streaming progress updates via SSE  
**Exports**: Async functions (determine_language_name, generate_initial_outline, etc.) and state machine construction  
**Imports**: operator, json, httpx, uuid, base64, LangGraph StateGraph/START/END, SSE utilities, LLM clients (OpenAI, Groq)  
**Patterns**: TypedDict state definition (StoryGenerationState), conditional routing (route_after_* functions), SSE event broadcasting via asyncio queues, state mutation through dict updates  
**Surprises**: State machine nodes appear to directly mutate shared state dict; no visible compensation/rollback logic; HTTP requests via httpx inside graph nodes; language determination logic embedded in node functions

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/graphs/avatar_generator.py**
**Purpose**: LangGraph orchestrator for character avatar generation, coordinating description generation, image generation, and database persistence  
**Exports**: Avatar generation workflow nodes (planner, generate_description, generate_image, update_database, decide_next_step)  
**Imports**: operator, TypedDict, LangGraph, UUID, httpx, Gemini client, Supabase client  
**Patterns**: Multi-step agentic workflow with decision nodes (decide_next_step) for conditional routing; Gemini API for image generation; image download and Supabase upload pattern  
**Surprises**: decide_next_step returns routing string but conditional logic not visible; image download via httpx into memory before Supabase upload; no error recovery per node

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/utils/sse.py**
**Purpose**: Server-sent events abstraction for streaming real-time updates to clients during long-running operations  
**Exports**: Async generators (sse_generator), utility functions (send_sse_event, format_sse, get_or_create_queue)  
**Imports**: asyncio, json, logging  
**Patterns**: Global dict of asyncio.Queue per client_id; format_sse encodes event name and JSON data; sse_generator yields formatted strings for FastAPI StreamingResponse  
**Surprises**: Queue cleanup (remove_queue) called manually — potential memory leak if not cleaned up; no heartbeat/ping mechanism visible; blocking operations in queue.get() could deadlock if consumer dies

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/utils/auth.py**
**Purpose**: Firebase token verification and Supabase user sync for federated authentication  
**Exports**: verify_firebase_token (dependency), get_or_create_supabase_user, get_current_supabase_user (dependency)  
**Imports**: fastapi Depends/HTTPException, Firebase Admin Auth, Supabase client, UUID  
**Patterns**: OAuth2PasswordBearer scheme; Depends() for route-level injection; UserData TypedDict for verified token payload; Supabase upsert for user sync  
**Surprises**: No visible token refresh logic; get_or_create_supabase_user creates user on first API call if not exists (implies async signup flow); family_id extracted from Supabase user metadata

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/utils/prompt_resolver.py**
**Purpose**: Dynamic prompt templating system with variable substitution, database caching, and config resolution  
**Exports**: resolve_prompt, get_prompt_config, invalidate_cache  
**Imports**: re, time, logging, Supabase client  
**Patterns**: Template string with {variable} placeholders; database lookup with in-memory cache dict; invalidate_cache for stale data; _fetch_prompt_from_db calls Supabase queries  
**Surprises**: Cache has no TTL — relies on manual invalidation; _fetch_prompt_from_db called on every resolve unless cached; no template syntax validation or error for missing variables

---

### **tuck-in-tales-backend/src/routes/stories.py**
**Purpose**: REST endpoints for story CRUD, generation orchestration, and real-time streaming  
**Exports**: Endpoints (list_stories, read_story, delete_story, generate_story)  
**Imports**: FastAPI, Depends (auth), UUID, LangGraph graph execution, SSE utilities, Supabase client  
**Patterns**: Dependency injection for authenticated user and family_id; background task execution for long-running story generation; SSE streaming via StreamingResponse; queue-based communication between graph and SSE  
**Surprises**: generate_story launches graph in background task but returns immediately with story_id; client polls SSE stream for progress; no visible idempotency token to prevent duplicate generation requests

